description:
A sports documentary about the Dunlop family - a motorcycling dynasty who have dominated the sport for over 30 years. Robert and Joey Dunlop were two brothers from a quiet rural part of Northern Ireland, both addicted to speed. It charts their rise to fame, and looks at how the family had to face the tragic death of Joey. Robert's sons William and Michael are also two leading riders continuing the family tradition today. The film includes stunning race footage, candid film of the riders behind the scenes, and a stunning narrative as told by the family.
